      "content": "but that's the thing... the people who \"know\" me are thousands of miles away. they only know the version of me that i post online. if i actually vanished, they'd just think i went off the grid or decided to travel somewhere else. it would just be a gap in a feed for a few days, and then they'd move on. it feels like i'm just taking up space that doesn't even belong to me.",
